/********************************************************************/
/**
 * 1.  GETTING STARTED
 **/

    @Package:       MyNews-FMan2
    @Creator:       Mike McMurray (alien@alienated.org)
    @Maintainer:    Mike McMurray (alien@alienated.org)

    Details:

    This Module is intended to extend the functionality of the
    MyNews-5 CMS (Content Management System) with a relatively basic
    web-based file manager.

    The files included with this MyNews-Module distribution are:

    $ MyNews-FMan2/README
    $ MyNews-FMan2/INSTALL
    $ MyNews-FMan2/UPGRADING
    $ MyNews-FMan2/htdocs/modules/display.php
    $ MyNews-FMan2/htdocs/modules/conf/fman2.conf.php
    $ MyNews-FMan2/htdocs/admin/fman2admin.php
    $ MyNews-FMan2/htdocs/admin/classes/fileupload.class.php
    $ MyNews-FMan2/htdocs/admin/lib/fman2admin.lib.php
    $ MyNews-FMan2/sql/MyNews-FMan2.help.sql

/********************************************************************/
/**
 * 2.  REQUIREMENTS
 **/

    - MyNews CMS Framework - >= 5-RC1

/********************************************************************/
/**
 * 3.  INSTALL
 **/

    - Please Refer to the included INSTALL file.

/********************************************************************/
/**
 * 4.  MISC
 **/

    This Module makes use of the iMarc PHP file upload class
    version 2.1.

    This class was modified to add certain functionality for use
    with the MyNews-FMan2 module.  The version included in this
    package is heavily modified and if upgraded outside of a
    MyNews-FMan2 release, will most likely break your installation.

/********************************************************************/
